Class ITimeValue

java.lang.Object
  com.xuggle.ferry.RefCounted
      com.xuggle.xuggler.ITimeValue

public class ITimeValue
extends RefCounted

Time (duration) values with units. This class also has methods that correctly account for long wrapping when comparing time values. Do not use.

equals

public boolean equals(Object obj)
Compares two values, returning true if the underlying objects in native code are the same object. That means you can have two different Java objects, but when you do a comparison, you'll find out they are the EXACT same object.

compareTo

public int compareTo(ITimeValue other)
Compare this timeValue to another. This compareTo will compare the values, but will assume that the values can never be more than half of int64_t's MAX_VALUE apart. If they are it will assume long wrapping has occurred. This is required especially if you're using TimeValue's as absolute time stamps, and want to know which is earlier.

Parameters:
other - the value to compare to
Returns:
-1 if this < other; +1 if this > other; 0 otherwise
